# Matches a US Social Security Number in the standard XXX-XX-XXXX format.
# Note that this only validates the shape of the number, not whether it is an
# SSN that has actually been issued (e.g. the area number 000 or 666 and the
# range 900-999 are never assigned). See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_Security_number
ssn = Regex(r"[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{4}")"}
